Programming Puzzles - Programming Challenge - Pete Goodliffe - ACCU 2025 Short Talks
---

Join us for "Programming Puzzles," a high-energy C++ programming quiz delivered as a lightning talk at ACCU 2025. In just five minutes, Pete Goodliffe challenges the audience with a rapid-fire series of programming concepts, turning this technical session into an interactive programming talk like no other.

This talk is part quiz, part code puzzle, and pure developer humor. Audience members are put on the spot to identify key software engineering and computer science terms — from recursion, pointers, and syntax, to binary trees, concurrency, and big O notation. Whether you're brushing up on coding terminology or testing your quick recall of data structures and debugging concepts, this talk delivers both laughs and learning.
